Package com.microsoft.azure.management.datalake.store.uploader

This package contains the classes for DataLakeStoreUploader.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FrontEndAdapter
    The frontend adapter that must be implemented in order to execute using the multipart uploader.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataLakeStoreFrontEndAdapterImpl
    A front end adapter that communicates with the DataLake Store.
    DataLakeStoreUploader
    Represents a general purpose file uploader into DataLake.
    MultipleSegmentUploader
    Uploads a local file in parallel by splitting it into several segments, according to the given metadata.
    SingleSegmentUploader
    Represents an uploader for a single segment of a larger file.
    StringExtensions
    A class of helpers to determine the location of record boundaries within byte arrays.
    UploadMetadata
    Represents general metadata pertaining to an upload.
    UploadMetadataGenerator
    An internally used class for generating the metadata used for upload.
    UploadParameters
    Represents parameters for the DataLake Uploader.
    UploadSegmentMetadata
    Represents metadata for a particular file segment.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SegmentUploadStatus
    Defines various states that a segment upload can have.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AggregateUploadException
    A wrapper for the exceptions that can be generated during parallel execution of the uploader.
    InvalidMetadataException
    Represents an exception that is thrown when the local metadata is invalid or inconsistent.
    UploadFailedException
    Represents an exception that is thrown when an upload fails.

Package com.microsoft.azure.management.datalake.store.uploader Description

This package contains the classes for DataLakeStoreUploader. The client used to efficiently and rapidly upload files into an Azure Data Lake Store account.
